Shanghai Taisheng Plans $15.3 Million Plant for Wind Towers

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-22T09:04:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/shanghai-taisheng-to-spend-100-million-yuan-on-wind-turbine-towers-plantt.html
Shanghai Taisheng Wind Power
Equipment Co. plans to invest 100 million yuan ($15.3 million)
in a factory to make towers for wind turbines in the western
region of Xinjiang.  The structures will be able to support turbines with a
capacity of between 2.5 megawatts and 5 megawatts each, the
company said today in a  filing  to the Shenzhen stock exchange.  The Chinese manufacturer said it will set up a unit to
manage construction of the production plant in Hami. It will use
30 million yuan of the investment as registered capital of the
unit, Xinjiang Taisheng Wind Power Equipment Co.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  